children.text: The hebel panel in this area has been cut, exposing the internal reinforcing steel inside the panel, which is not sealed and will rust over time causing damage and possible failure of the hebel panel.
The Hebel Power Panel external wall design and installation instructions state that
'Reinforcement exposed during cutting must be coated with a liberal application of Hebel corrosion protection paint' .
The section drawing below shows the steel reinforcement inside the panels;
This must be properly rectified to prevent failure of the Hebel system, prior to works in this area proceeding any further.
